From:bruwin
Hi CrazyPete ... Unfortunately you’ve drawn several conclusions without knowing
all the facts and taking good care to read exactly what I’ve said.

What I've said, in so many words, was the fact that my Investment Strategy was
based, to a very large extent, on what I learnt from Dr. Karl Posel. I've put
all of that into an Investment Package which I’ve sold to Investors for a
once-off fee. Included in the Package is an e-book copy of Dr. Posel’s first
book, ‘Winning on the JSE’. This book contains his first foray into advising
others what specific criteria to take into account before buying a stock. Since
he published that book, he’s seen the need to revise one or two of those
original criteria, plus he and I have added several new criteria, giving a
total of 12 in all that should be considered. My Package contains ALL of his
latest thinking, with those revisions, on the subject of stock market
investment, as well where to find vitally necessary stock screening and
financial statement information, free of charge, on the Net.

The point to remember is the fact that there are other enthusiastic Investors
out there who don’t necessarily have the Fundamental Analytical knowledge or
experience that the likes of you or other Board members may have, ... or may
have accumulated.
According to their feedback to me, they’ve found our information of great help
and they’ve all reported making more consistent profits than in the past.

With regard to books being "out of print", and your other inferences, I had to
get Dr. Posel’s permission to use and make public his works. He would therefore
share in the commercial venture. In addition, it wouldn’t be fair to those who
have paid for the information, to now find that it’s being freely disseminated
elsewhere on the Internet !
And ‘No’, it doesn’t sell books for Dr. Posel because he’s no longer interested
in involving himself in all that goes with re-prints, re-publishing etc.. for
not that much of a return for the writer. Most of a book’s profit goes to
publishers, printers, distributors etc.. You’d have to know him better to
appreciate his own motives and priorities in this regard.

However, many of his books are held by Libraries, both public, tertiary and in
Universities. He still gets many calls from enquiring investors and business
students.
He is currently busy writing a third book as a natural follow on to ‘Winning on
the JSE’ and ‘Enjoy Investing on the Stock Market’. He does it, these days,
largely for his own interest and he may or may not publish it for the reasons I
mentioned. I am encouraging him, however, to disseminate it via the Internet as
an E-book which will incur far less "loss" to third parties !

I "don’t dip into and out of the Market" that often because that’s the nature
of my Investment Strategy, as I attempted to outline in (a), (b) and (c) of my
Message 22953 to Paul Senior, and in 22853. I prefer to hold fewer, high
quality stocks which produce consistent profits and value for their
shareholders. In this regard you will find reference to 3 such stocks, HANS,
PDX and TWIN which earned 73% in 5 months, 34% in 10 months and 111% in 6
months respectively. In South Africa I've held 3 stocks for quite a while now.
These are DAW, DGC and WBO. They've collectively earned over 123% in 15 months.
Maybe that’s why others have been prepared to pay for my Investment Package !!

I’ve provided details of my comments about stocks in my Message 22847 to Suma.
I’ve been prepared to say what I like and what I don’t like .... and why.

A point to remember is that our strategy would go through over 8000 US
Industrial type stocks and narrow them down to, say, 6 to 10, which we would
then consider for purchase. This is contrary to the strategy of others, such as
maybe Dale Baker, who are proponents of holding larger, diversified portfolios
for risk and other considerations. It's our contention that this tends to
dilute profits.

I’m not, as a general rule, going to enter into this form of discussion in the
future. If you’d like to communicate with me in this regard, you’ll find me at
:-
bruwin90@yahoo.com
All communication to that address is done in strict confidence.

Best wishes with your investments in 2006.
"Strange Fish" (aka bruwin).
