From:Spekulatius
re stock screening - when i do a stock screen (I typically use the yahoo java
screener) my intention is to come up with a bunch of stocks (typically 30-50)
that are by some metrics cheap. in the particular case of the screen i used for
TWIN, P/B was one of the criteria, other were P/S, PE and debt/equity (as far
as i remember). Most of the stocks that meet the screening criteria are rubbish
and don't even pass a "30 sec smell" test. I use several different preset
screens and tend to tweak them to get more or less hit's. From time to time, I
have found stocks that have done very well, mostly because they had (in
additions to being cheap) some things going for it that were not evident ion
the screening criteria. In the case of TWIN for example, i noticed that the
company was supplying the oil industry (gears for oil drills) which i assumed
to be a very strong business.
