My biggest concern is I believe that a Katrina event is not a hundred year
event any more but rather may be a more common event in the future (i.e. earth
warming changes. Therefore, I wonder if the market is pricing in future
disasters that will result in higher operating costs for companies located on
this region? This is another reason to own a company that has geographical
diversification.

The last thing I want is to buy a company that was impacted by Katrina and find
out that another more powerful storm will hit in 18-24 months.

