Date:1/9/2006 3:35:21 AM
From:Spekulatius
CECO's gross margins look better because they allocated costs differently than
APOL. For CECO the G&A expenses are higher than the (direct) educational
expenses, for APOL the G&A is only about 125 of the direct expenses - so if we
assume that both run an similar business it's clear that these companies break
down their direct and indirect costs differently. For all i can see APOL has an
higher EBITDA margin which is what really counts 9at least for me).

Also note that CECO growth YoY growth for the last quarter only was about 10%
and slowed down considerably, whereas APOL growth still was about 20%.
